hereâ€™s a short clip from todayâ€™s weekly check-in on patreon.com/wokekindergarten is called, â€œWho gets to be a hero?â€ 

This week I talk about the theme of "heroism", and more specifically, as we are inundated with Western media's takes on the war in Ukraine, who gets to be a hero?

What narratives of heroism are being fed to us and how can we begin to have conversations with kids with "heroism" as an entry point?

In the FULL vid on Patreon, I offer ideas from a past unit I designed and implemented with my former Kindergartners called, Everyday Heroes vs Superheroes Through the Lens of Black History and Resistance.

I talk a bit about the difference between internal versus external power, manifestations of external power as imperialist practice and what traits are assigned to the people who "get to be" everyday heroes.

Friends, thank you for writing to me and I'm sorry that I can not answer everyone. Thank you for your support and special thanks for the photos of your work with our beats and miniatures. They warm our entire team, which is currently left without work and without a home.

Some of us took our families to a more or less safe place. But we will continue to help our friends and colleagues, many of them have small children or elderly parents who require our help during this difficult time. As soon as we can, we will definitely get back to work, and even if we fail to resume the physical production of goods, we will try to make STL files.

Many of you ask if we can provide STL files for sale of goods that were on sale. Unfortunately, this is not possible because at the moment they are in Zaporizhzhya and we do not have access to them.

In addition, we will try to provide our patrons with unique content and access to new STL works. I don't promise it will be soon, as our lives are now filled with phone calls, trying to buy essentials, and the sound of air raid sirens. But we will try. Several of our artists are already in a safe place and I think they will be happy to return to their favorite work to drive away terrible thoughts from themselves.

For those who asked how you can support us in addition to patreon, you can buy digital goods directly through our website. We are very glad for any support in this dark time, even a few kind words allow us to keep the hope that this nightmare will end and the world will stop the bloody killer who attacked our country.

https://www.patreon.com/Tortugabay

https://tortuga-gamestable.top/

During the evacuation, we united with our colleagues from Kharkov. They also make wonderful orc sculptures and would be grateful for any of your support.

https://wargamescrew.com/

Many people need my help, in addition, I am grateful for your support, most of my relatives were left without work and I am sure that I will have time to prepare a supply of water and provisions before the assault on the city by Russian troops begins (I hope the assault does not start). Russians are located 30 km from the city. Cities that find themselves on the front line or in the occupation zone of the Russians remain without food and water supplies.

Friends, thank you for your support! Understanding that we're not alone and that there are people that care is something that helps to live through those horrible days. In Ukraine temperature dropped below zero, with some snow - so no hope for fresh greens (managed to find some older grass, but it's a kind of miracle). Now veggies/special food delivery yet, so we're using older stockpiles we had. Can't imagine this in 21 century, but this is reality: half-empty shops, no medicine, in some cities there is no gas/electricity/heat - people are dying not just because of shelling, but also simply starving to death. Our thoughts are with Mariupol, which russia decided to destroy as example. Nightmare - but it came to life.
We're trying to stay online, to update you about our situation and about situation in our country.

Hello @doglikeaweapon Community! I got a little wound and so I got some time to make a new print that you have been asking me a lot about lately. This is a story about courage and honor.

"Russian warship, go fuck yourself!" was the last communication made by Roman Gribov, who was stationed on Snake Island (Ukraine) on 24 February 2022 during the Russian attack on the island. 

During the onslaught, one of the Russian warships taking part in the siege of the island called on the soldiers to surrender in exchange for safety, at which point, the defenders agreed to curtly decline the offer, and responded with the remark. Subsequently, Snake Island was captured by the Russian naval forces, and the thirteen soldiers defending it were thought to have been killed in the Russian assault.
 On 28 February 2022, the Ukrainian Navy posted on its Facebook page that all the border guards of the island were thought to be alive and detained by the Russian Navy. 

The phrase, and derivations of the phrase, became widely adopted during the 2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine.

This week, I spoke to journalist & activist Abby Martin about the spate of left media censorship that's occurred over the past few weeks. RT America, Russia's 24/7 English-language news channel, has been shuttered -- presumably because the cost of sanctions on Russia made it difficult to sustain, while RT has been banned entirely in Europe. Over 600 episodes of the show Abby hosted for 3 years at RT have been wiped from the internet, along with shows by other RT hosts like Pulitzer Prize winning journalist Chris Hedges & Lee Camp. Even The Hill was barred from YouTube last week, suggesting even corporate-backed news outlets aren't safe. Abby breaks down what happened, how left media can survive under capitalism, accusations of bias against Russia TV, her advocacy for Palestine rights, and what American media is getting wrong about Ukraine.

Friends, hello!

It's hard to pick words to say proper "thank you" for your love and support. 
It's important to believe in humanism and kindness - but it's sooo hard in this situation. Death, blood, destroyed lives. How can this be justified? People are tired, people are uncertain about "today" and "tomorrow". What russia does is bloody genocide (well, not the first time; read about Holodomor, when - by very optimistic calculations - Soviet Union and moscow killed 3 000 000 of Ukrainian people; realistic numbers bouncing between 5 000 000 to 10 000 000, entire villages died back that days; some witnesses of that crime still alive and are horrified this happens again in cities like Mariupol). So we don't have any illusion on "where russia is heading with that" and we're ready to continue our fight. How will russia clean up that blood? Have no idea, probably they still think money can buy indulgence. We really hope the world can say "no" to that thoughts. We really hope empire will fall one day. 
But for now Ukrainian hearts are broken to small pieces and we doing our best to put them together. With your love. And your support.

Donbas Frontliner after a small trip to Lviv come back to Kyiv now. We have plane to enlarge team and operation. Support us - www.patreon.com/donbasfrontliner (link also in bio)

At photos:
 1. Volodymyr - 60 years old fisher man from territorial defense with old Degtyaryov machine gun (1929) at the fire position.
 2. Civil volunteer build anti-explosion protection from sand bags around the monument of Grand Princess Olga, in the St. Michael's Square.
 3. Brothers from Territorial Defense at the road checkpoint in Vinnitsa region.
 4. Elena is making coffee. Not many coffee shops now working in Kyiv. And find open one - it is luck.
 5. The filters brought weapons for consecration in a taro Cossack vat.
 6. Shaman Siverets - Ukrainian army soldier after one month of heavy fight  in Irpin (few days of rest now).
 7. People spent time in cold bomb shelter in the center of Kyiv.
 8. Chechen figters. No face! A lot of relatives still in Ichkeria.
 9. Street food market not far from Irpin. It was a lot of heavy sounds when people try to buy some food.
 10. The tractor sows the fields in Vinnitsa region. Just 150 km from everyday heavy battlefields.

Prof Wolff explains how capitalism moves its powerful centers over time. Will the United States be the next country whose wealth and influence will move to another part of the world? History may be showing us that exact path lies ahead.

"We better understand that our position in the world has changed. And every event that happens: trade war with China by Mr. Trump goes nowhere,  Russia and the Ukraine, whatever the momentary event is. Its context, its frame is a reorganization of the world to take account of how capitalism has moved on. That's the real history, past and present, of the United States capitalist system." - Richard Wolff

This week, Briahna spoke to Seattle City Council member Kshama Sawant about the rash of Starbucks coffee locations unionizing around the country, why the Staten Island Amazon unionization effort was successful, the problem with some professional organizers, Chris Smalls' Tucker Carlson appearance, the difference between DSA and Socialist Alternative, how and why Kshama stays accountable to Socialist Alternative (and how the left could keep the Squad accountable), whether the Congressional Progressive Caucus's endorsement of Shontel Brown was the final straw for leftists hoping to change the Democratic party from with in, Socialist Alternative's position on Russia/Ukraine, and more. It's a rich, deeply reflective conversation, and you're going to want to listen through to the end.
